snippet: In “Birders: The Central Park Effect,” shown Monday on HBO, the birds — 117 species in all — get their own credits, in order of appearance.
abstract: HBO's Birders: The Central Park Effect was frustratingly difficult for the director and birder Jefferey Kimball to produce, due to the lack of cooperation from the 117 species of birds featured in the program.
lead_paragraph: In “Birders: The Central Park Effect,” shown Monday on HBO, the birds — 117 species in all — get their own credits, in order of appearance.
